BaseField.Name: Label License Type Instructions
BaseField.Text: Select the license type and a template to begin editing your letter or communication.

BaseField.Name: Merge Data Tokens Instructions
BaseField.Text: "Merge Data Tokens" (above) replaces token in this template with appropriate lookup date from the system.

BaseField.Name: Dynamic values
BaseField.Text: "Set Dynamic Values" (above) prompts for custom text used in some templates and will populate in the template upon clicking merge values.

BaseField.Name: Label Letter Instructions
BaseField.Text: Edit the letter and/or subject in the screen below.

BaseField.Name: lbl_buttonInstruction
BaseField.Text: Use "Save" to maintain changes. Then use "Print" to print a paper version of the letter and/or use "Send Email" to send as an email.

BaseField.Name: Label Data Tokens Instructions
BaseField.Text: The purpose of this tab is to show you available data that can be inserted into your letter. To insert the data put square brackets in the middle of your letter and the values of the label to the left of the field or colons.

BaseField.Name: Administrator Section Instructions Label
BaseField.Text: Instructions: This section is only visible to VaultAccess users. Check Administrator Override to remove read-only configurations and show all fields. Select Admin Save to save any changes without applying business rules. Remember to uncheck override and save before closing.

BaseField.Name: Label96
BaseField.Text: Instructions to fill in the Recipient Email if you have the email address: Fill this field with the recipient's email to be able to send them an email.

BaseField.Name: Label97
BaseField.Text: Instructions to fill in the Recipient Email field if you have the FormID, EmailFieldName and TemplateName: Fill these fields with the FormID, name of the field that contains the email and name of the template that contains the email address of the recipient to whom you want to send the email.
